column5: I finally used my XP50 under water cam this morning. Im very impressed with the out come.                 Looking forward to using it more now.
WOW!  These are VERY cool shots!!
really cool...   now somehow rig it for the hardwater season
I can't get the videos to play Brian, but the still shots are excellent !!
Some cool pictures!
Thanks guys. Lew I sent a few links pm.  Notice I used a leader? LMAO
Nice and clear Brian, very cool! I noticed that you were able to get footage of "The World's Greatest Sport Fish"... consider yourself fortunate. HH
Those are come cool videos, and the pictures are awesome! Now to some footage of a muskie in action.
very cool  photos are great
Very nice and clear Brian.  .Great shots and video!
way cool Brian lots of effort for spectacular results.  Thanks  Art
I'm surprised you couldn't hear me laughing all the way over here

cool shots - I have the same camera and keep meaning to try making some - silly question but were you just holding it in your hand, or did you have it rigged up somehow? I find its really easy to get your finger in the way of the lense if your not careful.
wicked
Thanks guys. Having some new fun with this under water stuff.  Out again this morning,and took more.
I just hold it in my hand. I find the biggest problem,is keeping the strap out of the picture.LOL
Im working on something for the fall steel head run. I have a few pools that I want to check out. As for ice fishing,we will see. BURRRRR.
Nice pics! You should ask mike about rigging, I'm sure he could offer up some tips
wow those are awesome pics
Cool pics Brian !!!!!
Those are awesome shots! What kind of camera was it again?
I guess you just looked at the pictures.
Very clear lake
IS THAT FUN OR WHAT!!!!
